2fa.directory.name: GitHub
2fa.directory.notes: Hardware tokens must have a backup method, either SMS or software token.

2fa.directory.name: GoDaddy
2fa.directory.notes: If hardware 2FA enabled, customer support by phone requires enabling back-up method.

2fa.directory.name: Google Nest
2fa.directory.notes: Non-migrated accounts only have SMS & Email 2FA available.

2fa.directory.name: Namecheap
2fa.directory.notes: Only one 2FA method can be active at any given time

2fa.directory.name: GeForce (Nvidia)
2fa.directory.notes: Email 2FA is always enabled.

2fa.directory.name: 1Password
2fa.directory.notes: Teams using Duo with 1Password can't enable other 2FA methods. Non-U2F Hardware tokens and custom software methods are only available through Duo.

2fa.directory.name: PayPal
2fa.directory.notes: Some methods of 2FA are only available in a few countries. Contact PayPal for more information.

2fa.directory.name: Shopify
2fa.directory.notes: U2F requires using a Shopify ID. U2F can't be used on the Shopify mobile app, the Shopify POS app, or the Shopify Inbox app.

2fa.directory.name: Yahoo Mail
2fa.directory.notes: Linked phone number required for 2FA.

2fa.directory.name: Roblox
2fa.directory.notes: U2F requires TOTP to be setup. U2F is currently only supported in web browsers.

2fa.directory.name: ING Bank Slaski [PL]
2fa.directory.notes: The first U2F key requires confirmation at a bank branch.

2fa.directory.name: Apple iCloud
2fa.directory.notes: U2F requires a minimum of two security keys to be registered.

2fa.directory.name: Apple
2fa.directory.notes: U2F requires a minimum of two security keys to be registered.

2fa.directory.name: X (Twitter)
2fa.directory.notes: SMS only available on select providers and for Twitter Blue members only.

2fa.directory.name: Standard Notes
2fa.directory.notes: Professional Subscription required to use hardware security key.

2fa.directory.name: Skiff
2fa.directory.notes: TOTP must be enabled to use a hardware token.

2fa.directory.name: Aha!
2fa.directory.notes: 2FA is only available through Duo.

2fa.directory.name: Fastmail
2fa.directory.notes: Setup requires SMS verification.

2fa.directory.name: University of Otago
2fa.directory.notes: U2F is available to staff only

2fa.directory.name: Mastodon
2fa.directory.notes: TOTP must be enabled to use a hardware token.

2fa.directory.name: Dropbox
2fa.directory.notes: Hardware 2FA requires also enabling Software or SMS 2FA as a back-up.

2fa.directory.name: Vanguard
2fa.directory.notes: Hardware based 2FA requires SMS / Phone call 2FA as a backup.

2fa.directory.name: Bitbucket
2fa.directory.notes: An SSH key must be associated with your account to enable 2FA.

2fa.directory.name: Bank of America
2fa.directory.notes: Mobile apps only use SMS 2FA

2fa.directory.name: Bitwarden
2fa.directory.notes: 2FA methods vary depending on price plan. SMS & Call requires Duo integration

2fa.directory.name: Kraken
2fa.directory.notes: Email 2FA is mandatory for all users but only requested for unknown devices

2fa.directory.name: LastPass
2fa.directory.notes: Availability of 2FA options depends on your account type. U2F is available through Duo integration on all plans. Yubico OTP is only available on paid plans.

2fa.directory.name: York University
2fa.directory.notes: 2FA via SMS or phone call can only be enabled by the support team.

2fa.directory.name: Perimeter 81
2fa.directory.notes: Hardware 2FA is only available via Duo.

2fa.directory.name: Proton
2fa.directory.notes: TOTP must be enabled to use a hardware token.

2fa.directory.name: Wikipedia
2fa.directory.notes: Currently limited to administrators (and users with admin-like permissions like interface editors), bureaucrats, checkusers, oversighters, stewards, edit filter managers and the OATH-testers global group.
